ernal model cards (TalentLens v3.1, WorkPulse v2.4) classified 'CONFIDENTIAL — Internal Use Only' and explicitly prohibited from external distribution.' Finding 6: 'Internal model cards exist (TalentLens v3.1, WorkPulse v2.4) and contain detailed architecture, hyperparameter, training data, and performance information, but are marked 'CONFIDENTIAL — Internal Use Only' and prohibited from external distribution. No evidence of external-facing technical documentation package meeting Article 11 requirements...'", "missing": "", "reasoning": "The memo explicitly notes that internal model cards are marked 'CONFIDENTIAL — Internal Use Only' and prohibited from external distribution, identifying this as a limitation for meeting external transparency/deployer-facing documentation requirements."}, {"id": "C-046", "verdict": "pass", "confidence": "high", "evidence": "Finding 7: 'AI Disclosure clause in Client Deployment Agreement (Section 9.3) reads: 'The Services incorporate artificial intelligence and machine learning capabilities. Client acknowledges that outputs generated by the Services are probabilistic in nature and should not be used as the sole basis for employment decisions...' This is a single-paragraph legal provision; it does not provide the structured, accessible, and deployer-specific information contemplated by Article 12, including: (1) intended purpose of the system in the client's employment context, (2) performance characteristics with metrics disaggregated by demographic category or job function, (3) known limitations and failure modes, (4) how the system should be appropriately used, (5) how to invoke human oversight or contestation mechanisms, (6) how to report performance issues or misuse.'", "missing": "", "reasoning": "The memo explicitly identifies Section 9.3 of the Client Deployment Agreement as insufficient for AI Act purposes, quoting the clause and enumerating six specific elements it fails to provide."}, {"id": "C-047", "verdict": "fail", "confidence": "high", "evidence": "", "missing": "The memo does not mention January 15, 2026 or any product roadmap freeze date anywhere in the deliverable.", "reasoning": "The PASS condition requires reference to the January 15, 2026 product roadmap freeze as a timeline constraint. This date does not appear in the deliverable."}]}

